serve in my church and community? Choose one concrete, specific response — not a vague intention — and write it down. Good learning ends in worship and obedience, not merely in notes; the test of this lesson is not the quiz but your life.</p>\n<h3>Summary</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Contextual Theologies is rooted in Scripture and must be tested against the whole biblical story, not one isolated verse.</li>\n<li>We read it with the historic and global church, holding conviction together with humility and charity.</li>\n<li>True understanding joins head and heart — text, confession and love.</li>\n<li>The aim is transformation: worship, character and faithful service, not information alone.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Reflect</h3>\n<p>Write two or three sentences explaining Contextual Theologies in your own words, as if to a friend who is new to faith. Then note one question you still have. Bring both to the supporting study, the video, and your cohort discussion.</p>', NULL, 9, 51, NULL, 6, 'Contextual Theologies'),
